(166, 'Acrylic Flower Book Vase', 'Accessories', 'About this item\r\nExperience a blend of culture and art with our Unique Acrylic Book-Shaped Vase. Drawing inspiration from \"The Language of Flowers,\" this vase adds a touch of refined elegance to your home decor.\r\n\r\n100% Acrylic\r\nEco-conscious Materials\r\n15L x 4W x 20H (cm)\r\n7.9 x 5.9 x 1.6 (inch)', 'Acrylic Flower Book Vase.WEBP', '500.00'),
(167, 'Self Reading Human Statue', 'Accessories', 'Self Reading Human Statue, Book Lovers Statue, Human Sculpture, Self Reading Human Abstract Statue,Bookshelf Decor, Decorative Human\r\n\r\n• Materials: These sculptures are all hand-painted and polyester.\r\n\r\n• Product size:\r\nWidth: 9.05 inches (23 cm)\r\nHeight: 9.05 inches (23 cm)', 'Self Reading Human Statue.WEBP', '525.00'),
(168, 'Wooden Bookshop Book Nook - Bookshelf Insert', 'Accessories', 'About this item\r\nA 3D Do-It-Yourself Wooden Book Nook for adding charm and character to your bookshelf: Local Bookshop edition! \r\n\r\nThis kit includes all the wooden materials and instructions you need to build your nook. So whether you\'re a fan of fantasy realms, cozy libraries, scenic landscapes, or just a book worm like myself, you will surely enjoy putting together this miniature masterpiece!', 'Wooden Bookshop Book Nook - Bookshelf Insert.WEBP', '3200.00'),
(169, 'Japan Cherry Blossom Alley Book Nook DIY Kit with LED', 'Accessories', 'About this item\r\nThis DIY dollhouse kit makes a great craft project and gift for both children and collectors!, by following step-by-step instructions in the manual.\r\nAll materials such as wood, paper, fabric, felt and plastic are included. You\'re really making this project from scratch.\r\nFor example, all furniture needs to be assembled, signs and decoration need to be applied and you\'ll make all the food yourself too.\r\nThis is the perfect DIY project for creative people who love miniature crafts.\r\nIt even includes LED lights, which you\'ll also have to install, to finish your tiny and realistic shop\r\nThis dollhouse features a very detailed interior design with lights that lighten this dollhouse in the dark.\r\nThe book corner kit is made of high quality wood, sturdy and durable. This handmade 3D mini bookcase insert is inspired by the beautiful Japanese cherry alley. The real scene setting perfectly restores the micro world in the corner of the book, making you feel like you are in the world of the book.\r\n', 'Japan Cherry Blossom Alley Book Nook DIY Kit with LED.WEBP', '4200.00'),
(170, 'Cozy Pot Reading Book', 'Accessories', 'About this item\r\nIntroducing our second Cozy Pot design, tailored for the book lovers in your life!\r\n\r\nOur pot perfectly captures the cozy feeling when you finally get the chance to dig in a good book', 'Cozy Pot Reading Book.WEBP', '590.00'),
(171, 'Yoda Inspired Bookend', 'Accessories', 'About this item\r\nMay the force hold all your books. This Star Wars Yoda inspired bookend keeps all your favorite reads in place. It is also an exclusive and special book holder to further decorate and organize your bookshelf.\r\n\r\nThis Star Wars Yoda-inspired bookend can become a great gift for those who like to keep books in a visible place or are Star Wars fans. It was rebuilt from the last version, now has bigger dimensions, making it more stable and capable of holding your books.\r\n', 'Yoda Inspired Bookend.WEBP', '430.00'),
(172, 'Custom resin lamp,Epoxy and Wooden', 'Accessories', 'About this item\r\nCustom resin lamp,Epoxy and Wooden Night Lights,Handmade gift,Home Decor,Ocean Resin Lamp,Birthday Gifts,Gifts for Mom,boyfriend gift.\r\n\r\nInside the lamp is an image of a mysterious ring containing the power of darkness, and surrounded by hands pointing towards the ring, it seems like everyone wants to possess that mysterious power. The resin lamp is meticulously crafted with intricate designs and rich colors, exuding a dark majesty. ', 'Custom resin lamp,Epoxy and Wooden.WEBP', '670.00'),
(173, 'Wooden Bookshelf, Wooden Book Bench', 'accessories', 'About this item\r\n-Wooden book bench is 100% natural.\r\n-Made of African walnut wood.\r\n-It is polished with natural oil. Absolutely no chemicals were used.\r\n-Thanks to the book bench, you can keep your books that you want to reach easily on the desktop without clutter.\r\n-It is a stylish and useful product thanks to the aesthetic appearance of wood and the practical function of the bookbench.\r\n-Dimensions\r\nfor small size ;36,5 cm * 15,5cm * 21 cm\r\nfor big size ;50 cm * 15,5 * 21 cm\r\n-Bookbench\'s depth is 12,5 cm\r\nheight is 12 cm.', 'Wooden Bookshelf, Wooden Book Bench.WEBP', '2500.00'),
(175, 'Anxiety Bookshelf Selected ,Miniature model bookshelves', 'Accessories', 'About this item\r\nIndulge in the charm of a meticulously crafted micro-library with our exquisite Miniature Bookshelf. Carefully curated with 400 miniature books, each adorned with an enchanting cover, this bookshelf transcends mere decoration to become a haven of serenity and creativity in your study or living space.\r\nImmerse yourself in the therapeutic art of organization as you arrange these tiny tomes by color, font, imagery, or author, turning the mundane task of tidying into a delightful journey of self-expression. Whether you seek solace from the stresses of daily life or wish to infuse your space with a touch of whimsy, our miniature bookshelf promises to captivate your senses and spark joy with every glance.\r\nCrafted with meticulous attention to detail, our bookshelf is more than just a piece of furniture; it\'s a portal to a world of imagination and wonder. The compact size allows for seamless integration into any space, from cozy nooks to elegant shelves, making it the perfect accent piece for book lovers and design enthusiasts alike.\r\nEmbrace the joy of creation as you design and redesign your micro-library, each arrangement a testament to your unique tastes and preferences. And should inspiration strike, simply shake the box and start anew, embracing the endless possibilities that our miniature bookshelf has to offer.', 'Anxiety Bookshelf Selected miniature model book.WEBP', '1880.00'),
(176, 'To the Stars who listen Night Light, Velaris Lamp', 'Accessories', 'PRODUCT DETAIL\r\nSize: Rectangle base 6x9 inch, Round base 5.5x5.5 inch\r\nThis kit include: 1 wood base, 1 acrylic sheet, 1 remote control, 1 cable wire.\r\n- Wooden Base: Pinewood block is processed by modern CNC technology. High-quality 2K gloss coating (waterproof, anti-moldy, anti-termite) ensures the durability of the wood.\r\n- Acrylic Sheet: Transparent, sturdy, durable, and easy to clean. Images are either UV printed on plastic.\r\n- Remote control for easy adjustment: Adjust the brightness, change the color or lighting modes, and turn on or turn off the lights with the remote control.\r\nLED lights with 16 RGB colors and 4 flashing modes (Flash, Strobe, Fade, and Smooth) for impressive lighting effect. LED light usage time: From 10,000 to 20,000 hours.', 'To the Stars who listen Night Light, Velaris Lamp.WEBP', '3500.00'),
(177, 'Bookends Tower Bridge Metal', 'Accessories', 'About this item\r\nElevate your bookshelf game with our unique Metal Bookends – the perfect fusion of metal decor and minimalist style! They make the ultimate gift for readers and book lovers, adding a touch of British charm with a modern twist to any space.Whether you\'re into tower bridges or just want some sleek metal room decor, these bookends are here to bridge the gap between functionality and art.Go ahead, build your literary skyline! Shop now. ', 'Bookends Tower Bridge Metal.WEBP', '600.00'),
(178, 'Owl Hanging Bookshelf, Macrame Book Holder', 'Accessories', 'Size\r\n100% cotton\r\n- Wood stick hanging width from 9.5\'\' - 26\'\' depends on the number of book\r\n- Height fixed hanging book macrame 29.5\'\' ~ 75cm (without book)\r\n+ 6 book - W:9.5\'\' x H:29.5\'\' (W:24cm x H:75cm)\r\n+ 8 book - W:12.5\'\' x H:29.5\'\' (W:32cm x H:75cm)\r\n+ 10 book - W:16\'\' x H:29.5\'\' (W:40cm x H:75cm)\r\n+ 12 book - W:19\'\' x H:29.5\'\' (W:48cm x H:75cm)\r\n+ 14 book - W:22\'\' x H:29.5\'\' (W:56cm x H:75cm)\r\n+ 16 book - W:26\'\' x H:29.5\'\' (W:65cm x H:75cm)', 'Owl Hanging Bookshelf, Macrame Book Holder.jpg', '2300.00'),
(179, 'Miniature Wooden Bookshelf with Mini Books', 'Accessories', 'About this item\r\nThis exquisitely crafted Miniature Wooden Bookshelf with Mini Books is the perfect addition for book lovers and decor enthusiasts. Handcrafted with meticulous attention to detail, this tiny bookshelf features a selection of miniature books neatly arranged within a sturdy wooden frame.\r\n\r\nDimensions: 50mm x 100mm x 61mm\r\n\r\nWeight: Approximately 240g (including mini book weight 20g)', 'Miniature Wooden Bookshelf with Mini Books.WEBP', '1000.00'),
(180, 'The Power of Habit\r\nWhy We Do What We Do in Life and Business', 'Self-Help', 'This book explores the science behind why habits exist and how they can be changed. Duhigg presents a framework for understanding and reshaping habits in both personal and professional settings.', 'The Power of Habit.jpg', '1200.00'),
(181, 'Atomic Habits', 'Self-Help', 'James Clear offers practical strategies for forming good habits, breaking bad ones, and mastering the tiny behaviors that lead to remarkable results. His approach focuses on the impact of small changes.', 'Atomic Habits.jpg', '1500.00'),
(182, 'How to Win Friends and Influence People', 'Self-Help', 'Dale Carnegie, known as \'the arch-priest of the art of making friends\', pioneered the development of personal business skills, self-confidence and motivational techniques. His books - most notably How to Win Friends and Influence People - have sold tens of millions worldwide and, even in today\'s changing climate, they remain as popular as ever.', 'How to Win Friends and Influence People.jpg', '1000.00'),
(184, 'Thinking, Fast and Slow', 'Self-Help', 'The guru to the gurus at last shares his knowledge with the rest of us. Nobel laureate Daniel Kahneman\'s seminal studies in behavioral psychology, behavioral economics, and happiness studies have influenced numerous other authors, including Steven Pinker and Malcolm Gladwell. In Thinking, Fast and Slow, Kahneman at last offers his own, first book for the general public. It is a lucid and enlightening summary of his life\'s work. It will change the way you think about thinking.\r\n\r\nTwo systems drive the way we think and make choices, Kahneman explains: System One is fast, intuitive, and emotional; System Two is slower, more deliberative, and more logical. Examining how both systems function within the mind, Kahneman exposes the extraordinary capabilities as well as the biases of fast thinking and the pervasive influence of intuitive impressions on our thoughts and our choices. Engaging the reader in a lively conversation about how we think, he shows where we can trust our intuitions and how we can tap into the benefits of slow thinking, contrasting the two-system view of the mind with the standard model of the rational economic agent.\r\n\r\nKahneman\'s singularly influential work has transformed cognitive psychology and launched the new fields of behavioral economics and happiness studies. In this path-breaking book, Kahneman shows how the mind works, and offers practical and enlightening insights into how choices are made in both our business and personal lives - and how we can guard against the mental glitches that often get us into trouble.\r\n\r\n', 'Thinking, Fast and Slow.jpg', '1800.00'),
(185, 'Daring Greatly', 'Self-Help', 'Daring Greatly is not about winning or losing. It’s about courage. In a world where “never enough” dominates and feeling afraid has become second nature, vulnerability is subversive. Uncomfortable. It’s even a little dangerous at times. And, without question, putting ourselves out there means there’s a far greater risk of getting criticized or feeling hurt. But when we step back and examine our lives, we will find that nothing is as uncomfortable, dangerous, and hurtful as standing on the outside of our lives looking in and wondering what it would be like if we had the courage to step into the arena - whether it’s a new relationship, an important meeting, the creative process, or a difficult family conversation. Daring Greatly is a practice and a powerful new vision for letting ourselves be seen.', 'Daring Greatly.jpg', '1500.00'),
(186, 'You Are a Badass', 'Self-Help', 'The first ever self-development book to help millions of people around the globe transform their lives using humor, irreverence, and the occasional curse word—now with an exclusive new chapter on the power of intuition and inspiring testimonials, as well as an updated foreword and listener\'s guide\r\n\r\nIn this refreshingly entertaining guide to reshaping your mindset and your life, mega-bestselling author and world-traveling success coach Jen Sincero serves up 28 bite-sized chapters full of hilarious and inspiring stories, sage advice, loving yet firm kicks in the rear, and easy-to-implement exercises to help you:\r\n\r\nIdentify and change the self-sabotaging beliefs and behaviors that stop you from getting what you want.\r\nShift your energy and attract what you desire.\r\nCreate a life you totally love. And start creating it NOW.\r\nMake some damn money already. The kind you\'ve never made before.\r\nBy the end of You Are a Badass, you’ll understand how to blast past what’s holding you back, make some serious changes, and start living the kind of life that once seemed impossible.\r\n\r\n', 'You Are a Badass.jpg', '1200.00'),
(187, 'Man\'s Search for Meaning', 'Self-Help', 'Viktor E. Frankl was a medical doctor at a psychiatric hospital in 1942 when he became a prisoner in Nazi concentration camps in World War II. In 1946, he published this book about his camp experiences and a method of psychotherapy he developed. Forty-five years later, it was still named one of the most influential books in the United States.\r\n\r\nPart One describes his three years in four Nazi concentration camps, which took the lives of his wife, father, mother, and brother. He closely observed inmates’ reactions to their situation, as well as how survivors came to terms with their liberation.\r\n\r\nPart Two, introducing logotherapy, is an academic discussion of the psychological reactions experienced by all inmates to one degree or another. It solidified Frankl’s early theory that humanity’s primary motivational force is finding meaning in one’s life.\r\n\r\nIn Germany, titled Ein Psychologe erlebt das Konzentrationslager, or A Psychologist Experiences the Concentration Camp, its title in the first English translation was From Death-Camp to Existentialism. As of 2022, this book has sold 16 million copies and been published in 52 languages.', 'Man\'s Search for Meaning.jpg', '1400.00'),
(188, 'Grit', 'Self-Help', 'Why do some people succeed and others fail? Sharing new insights from her landmark research on grit, MacArthur \"genius\" Angela Duckworth explains why talent is hardly a guarantor of success. Rather, other factors can be even more crucial, such as identifying our passions and following through on our commitments.\r\n\r\nDrawing on her own powerful story as the daughter of a scientist who frequently bemoaned her lack of smarts, Duckworth describes her winding path through teaching, business consulting, and neuroscience, which led to the hypothesis that what really drives success is not genius but a special blend of passion and long-term perseverance. As a professor at the University of Pennsylvania, Duckworth created her own \"character lab\" and set out to test her theory.\r\n\r\nHere, she takes listeners into the field to visit teachers working in some of the toughest schools, cadets struggling through their first days at West Point, and young finalists in the National Spelling Bee. She also mines fascinating insights from history and shows what can be gleaned from modern experiments in peak performance. Finally, she shares what she\'s learned from interviewing dozens of high achievers - from J.P. Morgan CEO Jamie Dimon to the cartoon editor of The New Yorker to Seattle Seahawks coach Pete Carroll.\r\n\r\nWinningly personal, insightful, and even life changing, Grit is a book about what goes through your head when you fall down and how that - not talent or luck - makes all the difference', 'Grit.jpg', '1500.00');
