(366, 'Pocket Guide Emergency Pediatrics fifth Edition', 'Education and Textbooks', 'About the Book:\r\n\r\nThis book is compiled for quick reference in emergency cases. It has proved its value for pediatric junior doctors in prompt diagnosis and treatment of sick children at times when experienced advice is not immediately at hand. It is aimed for students preparing for FCPS-II (TOACS), MRCPCH, DCH, MCPS, GPs and those who are otherwise involved in pediatrics. This latest edition covers chapters of fluids and electrolytes, ventilation, antidotes, and other important emergency topics. Some important topics have also been added such as child abuse and non-accidental injury, procedures, poisoning,  febrile neutropenia, tables, growth charts, emergency drugs with doses and appropriate protocol of antibiotics in various infections.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nAbout the Author:\r\n\r\nMuhammad Aslam Khichi is a Professor and Head of Pediatrics at Shaikh Zayed Postgraduate Medical Institute, Lahore. He has over 15 years’ experience of teaching and has written many other books on pediatrics. He has to his credit, a number of research papers published in both national and international journals.', 'Pocket Guide Emergency Pediatrics fifth Edition.WEBP', '895.00'),
(367, 'HEMATOLOGY ONCOLOGY HANDBOOK OF CANCER CHEMOTHERAPY PROTOCOLS 4ED', 'Education and Textbooks', NULL, 'HEMATOLOGY ONCOLOGY HANDBOOK OF CANCER CHEMOTHERAPY PROTOCOLS 4ED.WEBP', '2495.00'),
(368, 'THE UNOFFICIAL GUIDE TO ECGS', 'Education and Textbooks', 'The unique and award-winning Unofficial Guides series is a collaboration between senior students, junior doctors and specialty experts. This combination of contributors understands what is essential to excel on your course, in exams and in practice – as well as the importance of presenting information in a clear, fun and engaging way. Packed with hints and tips from those in the know, when you are in a hurry and need a study companion you can trust, reach for an Unofficial Guide.\r\n\r\nThe Unofficial Guide to ECGs is a straightforward yet complete guide to interpreting ECGs and easily translating this knowledge to clinical contexts.\r\n\r\nEdited by experts in cardiology, the book systematically goes through how an ECG is performed and what every part of the ECG tracing represents. It covers common conditions associated with ECG changes and explains the underlying pathophysiology of why these changes occur. An extensive collection of 40 clinical cases with fully annotated ECGs and 120 MCQs are included to allow readers to practise ECG interpretation.\r\n\r\nPrimarily aimed at medical students, this new book will also be useful for all those who may need to brush up on ECGs, including junior doctors, nurses, paramedics, physicians’ associates and advanced nurse practitioners.\r\n\r\nClearly defined and systematic structure that is accessible to new learners\r\nExplanations for every component of an ECG tracing and their changes to aid understanding and memorisation\r\n40 cases with real-life ECGs, ranging in difficulty from beginner to advanced, and clinically focused questions for the reader to test themselves\r\nReal-life fully annotated ECG images to clearly highlight features of ECG changes\r\n120 MCQs with detailed explanations of correct and incorrect answers alongside annotated and unannotated ECGs\r\nA handy quick reference guide at the end of book covers ECG basics and important changes for rapid revision on the wards', 'THE UNOFFICIAL GUIDE TO ECGS.WEBP', '1995.00'),
(369, 'MY MARVELLOUS MIND', 'Education and Textbooks', 'Do you ever find yourself struggling to connect with your child’s feelings? Do you feel like their mind is a completely different world from yours? Our amazing mental health journal for kids can be the perfect solution for you! Packed with engaging activities, this science-based journal will help your child develop essential Social-Emotional (SEL) skills including:\r\n\r\nHEALTHY EMOTIONAL EXPRESSION – To identify, express, and manage their emotions in healthier ways, teaching them to navigate their feelings and communicate them effectively.\r\n\r\nPOSTIVE THINKING AND SELF TALK – To catch negative thoughts and turn them into positive thinking, helping them to break free from negative thought cycles.\r\n\r\nSELF CONFIDENCE AND SELF ESTEEM – To believe in themselves and their abilities, empowering them to take on new challenges and pursue their goals with confidence.\r\n\r\nGROWTH MINDSET AND RESILIENCE – To treat mistakes as teachers and to know that their abilities can be improved with effort and practice.\r\n\r\nCOPING SKILLS – To use mindfulness and relaxation skills to manage stress, anger, and other challenging emotions in a positive way.\r\n\r\n Key Features:\r\n\r\nDeeper connection with your child’s emotions\r\nMental health importance\r\nDevelop social-emotional skills', 'MY MARVELLOUS MIND.WEBP', '1700.00'),
(370, 'Essential Communication Skills for Healthcare Professionals', 'Education and Textbooks', 'Elevate Your Healthcare Practice with Essential Communication Skills\r\nMastering Patient Engagement\r\nEffective communication is the cornerstone of healthcare provision. This book equips healthcare professionals with the essential skills needed to engage with patients empathetically and efficiently. Learn strategies to build rapport, active listening techniques, and non-verbal communication cues to enhance patient satisfaction and trust. Elevate your practice by fostering meaningful connections with those under your care.\r\nEnhancing Interprofessional Collaboration\r\nIn today’s multidisciplinary healthcare environment, seamless collaboration is vital for optimal patient outcomes. Discover how to communicate effectively within your team, bridging gaps between different specialties and departments. This book provides insights into conflict resolution, assertive communication, and fostering a culture of mutual respect, empowering you to work cohesively with fellow professionals.\r\nImproving Clinical Documentation Precision\r\nAccurate clinical documentation is crucial for patient safety, quality care, and legal compliance. Enhance your proficiency in documenting patient encounters with clarity and precision. Explore best practices for charting patient information, ensuring thoroughness while maintaining efficiency. Elevate your documentation skills to convey vital information accurately, facilitating continuity of care and informed decision-making', 'Essential Communication Skills for Healthcare Professionals.WEBP', '495.00'),
(371, 'PARAMOUNT PRIMARY SCHOOL ENGLISH GRAMMAR AND COMPOSITION MULTICOLOUR EDITION', 'Education and Textbooks9', 'Wren & Martin’s Primary School English Grammar & Composition is a grammar textbook designed to be used as a prequel to the highly popular English grammar reference book, High School English Grammar & Composition. This book provides ample guidance and practice in sentence building, correct usage, comprehension, composition, and other related areas to equip the learners with the ability to communicate effectively in English.', 'PARAMOUNT PRIMARY SCHOOL ENGLISH GRAMMAR AND COMPOSITION MULTICOLOUR EDITION.WEBP', '995.00');
